These three Latin metricians all maintain the doctrine of the metra daubata. Marius Victorinus, to be sure, in one part of the composite work ascribed to him, accepts the nine prototypes which appear in Hephaes- tion and argues, it should be noted, the claims of antispastic mette with special vigor, but elsewhere he follows the rival system.
